lcms: avoid NaN when building BT.1886 transfer curves

Backport of mpv 47f81c8d7e5e (fixes mpv#17439). After a Little-CMS change,
cmsDetectBlackPoint can return a black point whose X/Z are slightly negative
due to rounding; transformed into the source RGB space this yields negative
src_black channels, and pow(negative, 1/gamma) is NaN — poisoning the BT.1886
tone curve and rendering all SDR gray on the vo_gpu / libmpv-render ICC path.
Bound src_black below by 0 before the pow().

The iina-release/1.5.0 mpv this build uses predates the upstream fix.

--- a/video/out/gpu/lcms.c
+++ b/video/out/gpu/lcms.c
@@ -276,7 +276,7 @@
         // Build the parametric BT.1886 transfer curve, one per channel
         for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
             const double gamma = 2.40;
-            double binv = pow(src_black[i], 1.0/gamma);
+            double binv = pow(MPMAX(0, src_black[i]), 1.0/gamma);
             tonecurve[i] = cmsBuildParametricToneCurve(cms, 6,
                     (double[4]){gamma, 1.0 - binv, binv, 0.0});
         }
